The affected entries are DNS URLs.

The separate crawl is on the same machine utilizing another heritrix
instance under Setup.

I don't have access to ping on that machine, but I can tell you the
original crawl (still in progress) has visited the many of the seed
list hosts with the described error and received '1' - Successful DNS
lookup. This being the case it may end up collecting all pages desired
even with the error, since the surtfile accept list includes these
domains/hostnames.

I am presently trying to the view the local-errors.log and exceeds the
length viewable through the shell and through the Heritrix UI it is
taken quite a long time to display any searched results. I will spend
more time with that.

You asked the following:
Are both these messages appearing for the same seed? Have you changed
anything in your crawler, especially with regard to the
PreconditionEnforcer or FetchDNS processor modules?
--> Both message are appearing for the same seed in the Seed Report
through the Heritrix interface. If I go to the seeds-report.txt I only
get the '-1 NOT CRAWLED ...' entry.

Question:
Can I have it revisit the seed items through the GUI using "View or
Edit Frontier
URIs" link in the Console tab providing a filename with the seed items
and checking the 'Force revisit'
box?

Thanks,
Mike

On Nov 9, 2007 6:38 PM, Gordon Mohr <gojomo@...> wrote:
>
>
>
>
>
>
> mjjjhjemj wrote:
>  > I recently paused my crawl and added several seeds to the seed list.
>  >
>  > Viewing the seed report under the Reports tab I see the following
>  > displayed under 'Status Code and Disposition' for all the seeds just
>  > added:
>  > Heritrix(-1)-Domain unresolvable
>  > Seed has not been processed
>  >
>  > I setup a separate crawl with just the new seeds alone and all list
>  > the following under the Reports tab: Status Code and Disposition:
>  > HTTP-200-Success-OK
>  > Seed successfully crawled
>
>  Are the affected seeds DNS URLs or IP dotted-quad (eg. 208.70.27.35) hosts?
>
>  Is the separate crawl on the same machine? Can the success/failure
>  machines 'ping', 'nslookup', or 'dig' (at *nix shell) the seeds' hostnames?
>
>  Are there any other errors related to those URIs in the heritrix_out.log
>  or local-errors.log?
>
>
>  > My question is everything going OK with the first crawl where I added
>  > new seeds to the seed list. Is is supposed to display
>  > 'Heritrix(-1)-Domain unresolvable' if the 'Seed has not been processed
>  > yet'.
>
>  Unless this is happening repeatedly, it could just be a transient or
>  local DNS problem at the time of the initial try.
>
>
>  > If this is so is the reason that it still states the above due to the
>  > large queue (1106246 queued) that needs to be processed first before
>  > addressing the new seed items?
>
>  Unlikely. Each host gets its own queue, and DNS entries are placed in
>  front of everything else on that queue. If many other hosts are in
>  progress (monopolizing all the worker threads), the new seeds might not
>  be tried at all for a while -- but also would not show as any error.
>
>  Looking at the code, I can't see a path that could result in both
>  'Heritrix(-1)-Domain unresolvable' and 'Seed has not been processed yet'
>  displaying for the same seed, nor can I reproduce by trying to crawl a
>  made-up unregistered domain.
>
>  Are both these messages appearing for the same seed? Have you changed
>  anything in your crawler, especially with regard to the
>  PreconditionEnforcer or FetchDNS processor modules?
>
>  - Gordon @ IA
>
